WHAT IS PYTHON?
Python is a high-level,interpreted programming language known for its simplicity and readability.

A Little History:
• Created by: Guido van Rossum

• First released: 1991

• Current version: Python 3 (actively developed and widely used)

• Name origin: Named after Monty Python’s Flying Circus, not the snake 

Why it's popular:
> Easy to learn
> Versatile(web,data science,automation,AI,etc.)
> Large community & libraries

BASIC SYNTAX:
# Hello World in Python
print("Hello, world!")

# Adding two numbers
a = 5
b = 3
sum = a + b
print("Sum:", sum)
